  ${
    $d x A $.  $d x B $.  $d x C $.  $( x is dummy. $)
    addcan.1 $e |- A e. CC $.
    addcan.2 $e |- B e. CC $.
    addcan.3 $e |- C e. CC $.
    $( Cancellation law for addition.  Theorem I.1 of Apostol, p. 18. $)
    addcan   $p |- ( ( A + B ) = ( A + C ) -> B = C ) $=
      ( vx cv caddc co cn0 wceq cc wrex wi negex wcel wa wb axaddass mp3an3
      cleq12d mpan2 opreq2 syl5bir adantr axaddcom mpan cleq1d opreq1 addid2
      syl6eq syl6bi imp sylibd exp r19.23aiv ax-mp ) AGHZIJZKLZGMNABIJZACIJZLZB
      CLZOZGADPVAVFGMUSMQZVAVFVGVARVDUSAIJZBIJZVHCIJZLZVEVGVDVKOVAVGVKUSVBIJZUS
      VCIJZLZVDVGAMQZVKVNSVGVORVIVLVJVMVGVOBMQVIVLLUSABTEUAVGVOCMQVJVMLUSACTFUA
      UBDUCVBVCUSIUDUEUFVGVAVKVESZVGVAVHKLZVPVGUTVHKVOVGUTVHLAUSUGDUHUIVQVIBVJC
      VQVIKBIJBVHKBIUJBEUKULVQVJKCIJCVHKCIUJCFUKULUBUMUNUOUPUQUR $.
      $([21-Nov-94]$)
  $}

  $( Cancellation law for addition.  Theorem I.1 of Apostol, p. 18.  This
     proof illustrates how ~dedth3 and ~dedth3 can be used to convert
     the assumptions of ~addcan into antecedents.  This general
     method can be used to convert deductions into theorems as needed. $)
  addcant   $p |- ( ( A e. CC /\ B e. CC /\ C e. CC ) ->
                 ( ( A + B ) = ( A + C ) -> B = C ) ) $=
    ( cc wcel caddc co wceq wi cn0 cded opreq1 cleq12d birimd opreq2 cleq1d
    cleq1 bi2imd cleq2d cleq2 0cn elimel addcan dedth3h ) ADEZBDEZCDEZABFGZACFG
    ZHZBCHZIUEAJKZBFGZULCFGZHZUKIABCJJJULUFBJKZFGZUNHZUPCHZIUQULUGCJKZFGZHZUPUT
    HZIAULHZUJUOUKVDUHUMUIUNAULBFLAULCFLMNBUPHZUOURUKUSVEUMUQUNBUPULFOPBUPCQRCU
    THZURVBUSVCVFUNVAUQCUTULFOSCUTUPTRULUPUTAJDUAUBBJDUAUBCJDUAUBUCUD $.
    $([22-Nov-94]$)

  ${
    $d x y A $.  $d x y B $. $( ` y ` is dummy. $)
    negeux.1 $e |- A e. CC $.
    negeux.2 $e |- B e. CC $.
    $( Existential uniqueness of negatives.  Theorem 1.2 of Apostol,
       p. 18. $)
    negeux   $p |- E! x e. CC ( A + x ) = B $=
      ( vy cv caddc co wceq cc wreu wrex wa weq wi wral opreq2 cleq1d reu4 cn0
      negex wcel axaddass mp3an1 mpan2 cleqcomd sylan9eqr opreq1 addid2 syl6eq
      exp32 comm imp a1i r19.21aiv exp r19.22 syl6 com23 axaddcl risset sylib
      mpd r19.23aiv ax-mp w3a addcant cleq2 biimparc syl5 rgen2 pm3.2i mpbir )
      BAGZHIZCJZAKLVQAKMZVQBFGZHIZCJZNZAFOZPZFKQAKQZNVQWAAFKWCVPVTCVOVSBHRSTVRW
      EVTUAJZFKMVRFBDUBWFVRFKVSKUCZVOVSCHIZJZAKMZWFVRPWGWFWJVRWGWFWIVQPZAKQZWJV
      RPWGWFWLWGWFNZWKAKWMWKPVOKUCZWGWFWKWFWGWKWFWGWIVQWGWINWFVPVTCHIZCWIWGVPBW
      HHIZWOVOWHBHRWGWOWPWGCKUCZWOWPJZBKUCZWGWQWRBVSCUDDUEEUFUGUHWFWOUACHICVTUA
      CHUICEUJUKUHULUMUNUOUPUQWIVQAKURUSUTWGWHKUCZWJWGWQWTVSCVAEUFAWHKVBVCVDVEV
      FWDAFKWSWNWGWDWSWNWGVGVPVTJZWCWBBVOVSVHWAXAVQVTCVPVIVJVKDUEVLVMVN $.
